name: T Chris
text: Wow...such a great time for my young family (wife and kids 10 and 8) this morning.  We did a 5 hr trip with Captain Scott and the time flew by as we were having a great time.  Scott is a great guide, very knowledgeable, and patient/helpful to put us all in position to catch fish.....and that's what we did.  Many Redfish & Trout and some others....and then my 10 yr old landed a 40lb black drum after a 10 min fight to bring him in (thanks to some coaching from our guide!) On top of great fishing, Scott has a good eye to spot dolphins and we got some great up close sightings of a pod of dolphins feeding a short distance from the boat!  Really awesome to see!  We are not experienced fisherman....just beginners and this was really fun.  Highly recommend when visiting Gulf Shores!

name: Alan Miller
text: Had the best time fishing and talking and told a few jokes. I limited out on red fish and my wife caught a monster black drum. Cant wait for the next trip.  Thanks for great memories.

name: John the Baptist
text: My girlfriend, her father, and I all boated around with “Scott” this morning. We’re on vacation here in Gulf Shores for the week and were just looking for a laid back fishing venture. Scott assured our time was spent well; we caught many red fish, black drum and some speckled trout. My girlfriend and I know very little about fishing, but Scott was eager to serve us. By the end of the trip, I felt as though Scott were more of a friend, than a fishing guide. We HIGHLY recommend Scott as a fishing guide; We’ll likely come back to see him next time we visit Gulf Shores.

text:
I have fished with Little Lagoon Fishing "Scott" for the last three years. I have fished for many years and many places this is by far the best fishing experiences I have ever experienced. Scott is very passionate and takes pride in his charter business, Scott makes you feel very welcome to be on his boat, not only does he not give up he works as hard as he can to put a fish on your hook. Not only does he make you feel welcome he, Scott always puts safety first to make sure you are well taken care of.

Looking forward to seeing you next time buddy.
Thanks, Brad.

text:
I have been on numerous charter trips and yes there are some competent boat captains  available and will likely supply an “ok” fishing experience for  you and your family but if you are  seeking a fantastic  trip with an exceptional
Captain  and Deckhand then you must go ahead and get booked on “Hooked Up”.  Me and my family, 6 total,  took a 6 hour trip targeting snapper we limited out  and moved on to other species. The deckhand works his butt off. Deckhand “Blake“  was like a little Tasmanian Devil on the deck. The Captain was so gracious and accommodating, my boys felt right at home on Captain Mikes beautiful Topaz. Captain and crew went out of there way to show my peeps a wonderful time. Lots of laughter and  new memories made on this trip. We had a blast. I hope anyone that books based on my review has a wonderful time like we did. We will be booking with these guys again. My wife is also posting a review as you check out our collective pictures you can tell we had lots of fun and did a lot of clowning around. Just look at the size of this king. Lol 😝

We caught our limit of very large Trigger fish and lots of bee liners. Had a great experience and would recommend him to anyone looking to have fun going fishing offshore!

name: Caroline Jackson
text: Captain Mike and his awesome deckhand, Blake, offered us one of the best weekend's we've had fishing here in Orange Beach. Captain Mike was just as eager as we were to catch some good fish, and that is exactly what we did the entire time! We limited out with no problem after he continuously took us to spots where the fish were biting. Both Captain Mike and Blake were on top of everything all day long, making it easy and also relaxing for us. The boat was beautiful, clean, and comfortable, but their company was the best of all. If you're looking for a fishing guide that won't let you down, Hooked Up Fishing is the only way to go. I highly recommend booking with them, and truly hope my family and I get to fish with them again one day.

text: Went out today with Captain Mike and his deck hand Blake. This was my wife’s first ever deep sea fishing experience and it was phenomenal!!! We caught plenty of red snapper and my wife caught a small bull shark (she thought it was Jaws!).  Mike and Blake were great to fish with and very professional. I would highly recommend Hooked Up Charters for your next fishing experience in Gulf Shores!!!

name: lisa downard
text: I have been on several fishing charters but this was by far the BEST experience we have ever been on.  Captain Michael Thomas and deck hand (Blake) went out of their way to make it a perfect day.  They put us on the fish immediately.  If we spent a few minutes with no bites he was quick to move us to a better spot.  The deck hand (Blake) was so attentive.  Us girls never had to touch bait or wait for bait.  He was always ready and we kept him very busy.  They were fun to spend the day with even if we hadn’t caught fish.  When it was time to head back in the captain saw a spot with great potential for Mahi-mahi so he had us drop some lines.  My boys were sooo excited to catch mahi-mahi, king mackerel and lots of red snapper.  We will definitely go on this boat again!  Worth every dollar!

He didn't offer to order it in or to order it on-line. I was willing to do either.
The boat and ATV guy lost a sale  since they could not break free from their conversation to help me. I hate pushy sales people but at least acknowledge me after you see me taking pictures and returning to the same area 3 times.
I never saw anyone in the clothing departments so I didn't get the items that I wanted  to stock up on.
I return to Bass Pro because of the quality of the products and it is normally easy to get help. I did not find that at this store.
It was a surprise to find the outside water features seemed neglected too.  I  didn't see any fish and the fountains and falls that are normally seen were not there either.
Luckily I can find another store close by to get what I'm looking for.
I spent FAR less than I normally do at THIS Bass Pro store and I still need to do my spring shopping.
I will not return to this store if I can another one close by.

Please understand that this store is not exactly bad, it just doesn't have the warm welcoming flow and energy that I have grown fond to.

The usual point of sale goodies can be found at every register, but the real goodies are found in the old time store... The fudge is awesome!  Sit down meals and available at the in-store restaurant offering a variety of animal meats.

I was impressed with the knowledge the staff had in their respective departments. The gun area had well trained staff and offered many hints on the model I was interested in.  My wife hit the women's clothing like a fire sale and found some great outfits.

This store is very accessable to those people with disabilities. The elevators are great for those of us with bad knees.

This place gets a big five star rating.

I went upstairs and took the long way to get there.  We were greeted properly walking in so didn't see any reason to think anything else.  We walked through the bows, then walked past the rifle racks to the scopes.  The guys working the counter were working with other customers so I looked around, I found the one I wanted to see.  In that process, I found another that I was interested in I looked up to see the status of the salespeople and they were over on the other side talking to each other and what looked to be looking at a phone behind the counter.  I left the counter went to check on kids who were by the aquarium.  We walked around and I decided I was going to get both of the scopes I found.  I went back and both salespeople were talking to one person.  So while I was waiting, I found a third scope I wanted.  The lady they were talking to left and they went back to the other end of the counter and did what they were doing before.  Now I don't like when a salesperson hovers over me, but I have worked in retail enough to at least let a customer know I am there to help.  I couldn't even get that out of them, so we walked away.  They missed a out a $4K sale.  I am not going to beg for them to help me.  They weren't busy.  The way I see it is they were just busy ignoring me.  Walking to the exit, I found a gear bag for a decent price and decided to buy it.  The man at the cash register was awesome.  If the guys at the gun counter were, Bass Pro would have sold me a lot more than a $12.99 bag.  I will go back again.  Like I said, this was the first time I had a bad experience there.

text:
Extremely friendly and knowledgeable family.
They absolutely love to talk fishing.
Bought waders and boots for my wife and they took all the time she needed to make the right choice for her.

While my wife was trying on the waders & boots I learned a few things I was doing wrong chasing stripers on the lake from Mary Carole. Who incidentally just finished a guide trip with a client that landed a 20" rainbow!

Brandon and Mary run a great shop. Plenty of fishing gear and tying supplies.
They're quite a ways from our place in arley but I, and now my wife, really enjoy getting down there when we can.

Highly recommended whether you're a complete newbie or a seasoned veteran.

Cannot recommend this place enough! Booked a half-day wading trip to start learning how to fly fish and it was even better than I had hoped for!

Brandon is a fantastic guide who was incredibly patient and broke everything down in a very straight forward manner, making it easy to make decent casts and start working to get better. He took the time to teach us stuff so that we could come back and fish on our own.

You can tell he his guide service is VERY kid friendly!

I cannot wait to work on the stuff he taught us and take another trip to get additional instruction!

****edited: I was able to work my way back on my own to fish the same river and caught two beautiful rainbows on my own! Second trip fly fishing and I have to give credit to the guiding service because without the initial lesson I wouldn’t have figured it out so quick!!!
